WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.260
The Learning Python with the Python Academy Workshop tries to keep you engaged in the

00:00:10.260 --> 00:00:12.860
learning process over several weeks.

00:00:12.860 --> 00:00:17.760
This approach helps to reinforce your understanding and retention of the material, while also

00:00:17.760 --> 00:00:22.260
allowing you to interact with experienced instructors who can provide personal guidance

00:00:22.260 --> 00:00:24.139
to help achieve your learning goals.

00:00:24.139 --> 00:00:29.200
The attractive thing about this workshop is that it is a POSIT Academy course.

00:00:29.200 --> 00:00:34.080
That means you'll learn by doing a six-week online apprenticeship with a POSIT mentor

00:00:34.080 --> 00:00:35.080
and several co-apprentices.

00:00:35.080 --> 00:00:41.639
You'll meet as a group twice a week to work through a realistic project and to get feedback

00:00:41.639 --> 00:00:43.240
on your work.

00:00:43.240 --> 00:00:47.680
At the first meeting each week, you'll have a chance to just work together and ask questions

00:00:47.680 --> 00:00:50.160
with your mentor and your fellow students.

00:00:50.160 --> 00:00:54.360
At the second meeting, you'll present your work to everyone else.

00:00:54.360 --> 00:00:58.000
This meeting is not optional, but it's the place where you'll get the personalized

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:01.919
feedback that will help you become a better data scientist.

00:01:01.919 --> 00:01:05.959
In between the meetings, we'll give you interactive tutorials that you can complete to learn the

00:01:05.959 --> 00:01:09.320
materials for next week's part of the project.

00:01:09.320 --> 00:01:12.839
As the project draws to an end, it'll be time for conference.

00:01:12.839 --> 00:01:17.519
We'll see you there in person during the workshop days and we'll finish up the project

00:01:17.519 --> 00:01:18.519
together.

00:01:18.519 --> 00:01:19.519
I hope to see you there.

00:01:19.519 --> 00:01:26.279
Hi, I'm Sisa Madhikari and I'm one of the content writers here at Academy.

00:01:26.279 --> 00:01:30.080
Learning with Academy is both fun and effective.

00:01:30.080 --> 00:01:34.120
Because the courses are spread over a couple of weeks, you never feel like you're drinking

00:01:34.120 --> 00:01:35.760
from a firehose.

00:01:35.760 --> 00:01:41.519
You have time to truly understand a concept before moving on to the next, but it is more

00:01:41.519 --> 00:01:44.720
social than a purely online course.

00:01:44.720 --> 00:01:50.440
You get to meet the same small group of students and mentor each week, so it's a more fun and

00:01:50.440 --> 00:01:52.519
supportive way of learning.

00:01:52.760 --> 00:01:57.519
Python has a thriving community of tools and packages that can be overwhelming for beginners.

00:01:57.519 --> 00:02:02.199
At Academy, we strive to simplify the learning process by providing a more structured and

00:02:02.199 --> 00:02:05.360
opinionated approach to learning Python.

00:02:05.360 --> 00:02:10.039
Our focus is on teaching learners how to think about processing data, rather than just how

00:02:10.039 --> 00:02:11.639
to write code.

00:02:11.639 --> 00:02:15.600
This approach requires a longer engagement period compared to traditional workshops,

00:02:15.600 --> 00:02:20.639
but provides learners with more flexibility to learn from each other about code approaches

00:02:20.639 --> 00:02:22.500
and new packages.

00:02:22.500 --> 00:02:27.380
As a result, learners can tap into the Python community with confidence and continue to

00:02:27.380 --> 00:02:29.100
build on their data processing skills.

